%N A393901 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = (2*n + k - 1) * 2^(k-2).
%H A393901 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A393901/b393901.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..11325</a> (rows n = 1..150, flattened)
%H A393901 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A393901/a393901.png">Log log scatterplot of a(n)</a>, n = 1..11325 (150 rows).
%H A393901 Aitzaz Imtiaz, <a href="/A393901/a393901.jpg">Hand-drawn diagram</a>.
%e A393901 Triangle T(n,k) begins:
%e A393901   1;
%e A393901   2,  5;
%e A393901   3,  7,  16;
%e A393901   4,  9,  20,  44;
%e A393901   5, 11,  24,  52,  112;
%e A393901   ...
%p A393901 T:= (n, k)-> (2*n+k-1)*2^(k-2):
%p A393901 seq(seq(T(n, k), k=1..n), n=1..11);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 02 2026
%t A393901 Table[(2*n + k - 1)*2^(k - 2), {n, 11}, {k, n}] // Flatten (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Mar 02 2026 *)
%o A393901 (Python)
%o A393901 def T(n, k):
%o A393901   return int(int(2*n + k - 1) * 2**(k - 2))
%o A393901 seq = []
%o A393901 for n in range(1, 12):
%o A393901   for k in range(1, n + 1):
%o A393901     seq.append(T(n, k))
%o A393901 print(seq)
%Y A393901 Cf. A053220 (right diagonal), A053218, A053219.
